Description: A fragment of a clay jar-seal: in a good state of preservation, bearing part of an impressed inscription giving the name Ka.
Curator's comments: Bibliography: W. M. F. Petrie, 'Royal Tombs of the Earliest Dynasties' II, 19, 48, 30, 51, pl.II, 1, pl.XIII, 89; P. Kaplony, 'Die Inschriften der Ägyptischen Frühzeit, I (Wiesbaden, 1963), 62; P. Kaplony, 'Die Inschriften der Ägyptischen Frühzeit, II (Wiesbaden, 1964), 720, n. 210.
